  <p>Ardunio Software (IDE) is a program that allows you to code your Jewelbot on your computer! </p>

<h3>LINUX USERS ONLY STEP</h3>
  <p>You may not have access to the USB port. You need to be a member of the "dialout" group. Add yourself via the command prompt. </p>
  <p>ONLY tested for Ubuntu 16.04 LTS - should possibly work for recent Ubuntu versions though.</p>
  <ol type="a">
  <li>First check if you are a member of that group:</li>
    <ol type="1">
      <li>groups ${USER}</li>
      <li>This will list all the groups you belong to.</li></ol>
  <li>If you don't belong to the dialout group then add yourself to it, for example:</li>
      <ol type="1">
        <li>sudo gpasswd --add ${USER} dialout</li></ol>
  <li>You then need to resart your computer again for it to be effective.</li></ol>

